      • createAssetCreateOperation

        public Cancelable createAssetCreateOperation(AccountObjectId issuer,
                                             java.lang.String symbol,
                                             byte precision,
                                             java.lang.String description,
                                             AssetOptions options,
                                             MonitoredAssetOptions monitoredOptions,
                                             Fee fee,
                                             Callback<ch.decent.sdk.model.operation.AssetCreateOperation> callback)

        Create asset create operation. For more options see class AssetCreateOperation constructor.

        Parameters:
        issuer - account id issuing the asset
        symbol - the string symbol, 3-16 uppercase chars
        precision - base unit precision, decimal places used in string representation
        description - optional description
        options - asset options
        monitoredOptions - options for monitored asset
        fee - class Fee fee for the operation, by default the fee will be computed in DCT asset. When set to other then DCT, the request might fail if the asset is not convertible to DCT or conversion pool is not large enough
        callback - a callback object that asynchronously receives the result value or error
        Returns:
        a request handler object which can be used to cancel the request
        See Also:
        class AssetCreateOperation
